{
    "name": "Vakyansh ASR - Kannada",
    "description": "Vakyansh aims to host the key essentials of Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) technology, focusing on Indian languages. It is a resource that allows people to build applications that leverage speech recognition. These models are built using the wav2vec 2.0 architecture. We use a self supervised learning approach in which speech representations are learnt in a latent space by masking during audio pretraining. We pretrained on almost 10,000 hours of data in 23 Indic languages. The subsequent ASR models are then finetuned on labelled data.",
